00:30:38.063 --> 00:30:40.732
Look.
I'll meet you on the plane.

482
00:30:40.816 --> 00:30:42.484
Just text me
which one you're on.

483
00:30:42.568 --> 00:30:44.611
- Keep moving.
- It's okay.

484
00:30:44.695 --> 00:30:47.114
He'll be right back. Okay?

485
00:30:47.197 --> 00:30:48.699
We're gonna put this in here.

486
00:30:52.244 --> 00:30:54.913
Let's go. let's go. let's go.

487
00:30:54.997 --> 00:30:56.915
No. I need to grab
something from the car.

488
00:30:56.999 --> 00:30:58.792
I have my wristband.
Can I get back in?

489
00:30:58.876 --> 00:31:00.002
Yeah. go ahead. Go.

490
00:31:00.085 --> 00:31:01.086
Okay.

491
00:31:05.257 --> 00:31:06.300
All right.

492
00:31:14.725 --> 00:31:16.393
You know what?
Come here. Come here.

493
00:31:17.102 --> 00:31:18.937
Hey! Excuse me.

494
00:31:19.021 --> 00:31:21.023
Look. I know my husband
just talked to you.

495
00:31:21.106 --> 00:31:23.483
He's going back to the car
to get my son's meds.

496
00:31:23.567 --> 00:31:26.069
- Can you make sure he gets on our plane...
- Meds?

497
00:31:28.071 --> 00:31:29.448
Yeah. It's just his insulin.

498
00:31:30.073 --> 00:31:31.116
Sergeant Ruiz?

499
00:31:31.200 --> 00:31:32.534
What's the problem?

500
00:31:32.618 --> 00:31:33.827
What's up?

501
00:31:33.911 --> 00:31:35.495
It's okay.
I just explained to him.

502
00:31:35.579 --> 00:31:37.956
It's just for his insulin pump.
It's not a big deal.

503
00:31:39.499 --> 00:31:41.627
You know what? Forget it.
It's fine. We don't need it.

504
00:31:41.710 --> 00:31:43.587
That's not the issue. ma'am.

505
00:31:43.670 --> 00:31:45.797
Don't worry about it. We'll use the shots.
It's not a big deal.

506
00:31:45.881 --> 00:31:47.382
- Line one. we need an escort.
- What?

507
00:31:47.466 --> 00:31:50.385
Look. we have the bracelets.
We were selected.

508
00:31:51.178 --> 00:31:52.471
Follow me.
please. ma'am.

509
00:31:52.554 --> 00:31:54.264
No. no. no. Why?

510
00:31:54.348 --> 00:31:55.933
Ma'am. I'm not asking.

511
00:31:57.684 --> 00:31:58.894
Let's go.

512
00:32:03.523 --> 00:32:04.524
It's okay.

513
00:32:21.083 --> 00:32:23.210
- Come on. Hurry up!
- Over here!

514
00:32:23.293 --> 00:32:25.837
No. Captain.
I don't remember giving the order on that.

515
00:32:25.921 --> 00:32:28.257
No. tell me something.
how is there a problem with that manifest?

516
00:32:28.340 --> 00:32:30.384
I signed for it myself.

517
00:32:30.467 --> 00:32:33.845
Then I will come down there and check it.
I'll be down there in five.

518
00:32:35.681 --> 00:32:37.891
- The kid's diabetic.
- Don't touch him.

519
00:32:37.975 --> 00:32:40.269
I'm sorry.
You should've been informed.

520
00:32:40.352 --> 00:32:42.729
Anyone with a chronic condition
can't be on the plane.

521
00:32:42.813 --> 00:32:44.606
It's just diabetes.

522
00:32:44.690 --> 00:32:47.025
His condition should've
been flagged at screening.

523
00:32:47.109 --> 00:32:49.903
If I hadn't said anything to the
guard. he'd have no idea he had a pump.

524
00:32:49.987 --> 00:32:51.822
There's nothing I can do
about that. ma'am.

525
00:32:51.905 --> 00:32:54.658
You can pretend
that you didn't see it.

526
00:32:54.741 --> 00:32:57.869
- Ma'am. I didn't write the rule. Sorry.
- Then ignore it!

527
00:32:59.454 --> 00:33:01.248
What if this was your family?

528
00:33:04.918 --> 00:33:07.045
My family wasn't selected.
ma'am.

529
00:33:09.589 --> 00:33:12.009
99 % of armed forces weren't.

530
00:33:12.092 --> 00:33:15.053
We are all volunteers here
just doing our jobs.

531
00:33:15.721 --> 00:33:16.847
I'm sorry.

532
00:33:19.308 --> 00:33:20.309
I am.

533
00:33:22.102 --> 00:33:24.062
But please...

534
00:33:24.146 --> 00:33:27.441
His father. my husband.
is on one of those planes right now.

535
00:33:27.524 --> 00:33:29.151
What am I
supposed to do?

536
00:33:37.409 --> 00:33:38.410
Hey!

537
00:34:01.808 --> 00:34:02.976
This is Breen.

538
00:34:04.061 --> 00:34:05.520
Yeah. I'm looking
for a passenger.

539
00:34:06.980 --> 00:34:08.357
Ma'am. what's his name?

540
00:34:08.440 --> 00:34:09.941
John Allan Garrity.

541
00:34:10.025 --> 00:34:11.485
John Allan Garrity.

542
00:34:12.694 --> 00:34:13.695
Chalk 33?

543
00:34:15.489 --> 00:34:17.074
Yeah. his son was flagged.

544
00:34:17.157 --> 00:34:18.784
Thank you.
They're looking for him.

545
00:34:18.867 --> 00:34:21.244
Thank you. Thank you.

546
00:34:31.338 --> 00:34:32.631
Allison!

547
00:34:33.673 --> 00:34:34.674
Nathan!

548
00:34:35.842 --> 00:34:36.968
Allison!

549
00:34:45.811 --> 00:34:49.064
Do not run. Move in an orderly
fashion to your designated aircraft.

550
00:34:49.147 --> 00:34:52.109
Have you seen a kid? He's age seven.
He's wearing a gray hoodie.

551
00:34:52.192 --> 00:34:54.861
And his mom is dark-haired.
She's about 5'7".

552
00:34:54.945 --> 00:34:57.239
I've seen a lot of kids. sir.
Please keep moving.

553
00:34:57.322 --> 00:34:59.449
I need to know
if they made it on first.

554
00:34:59.533 --> 00:35:01.993
- Do they have bracelets?
- We all have them. yeah.

555
00:35:02.077 --> 00:35:03.829
Then they're on
one of these planes.

556
00:35:03.912 --> 00:35:06.081
Are you sure they're all
going to the same place?

557
00:35:06.164 --> 00:35:07.499
Yes. Now go.

558
00:35:08.583 --> 00:35:11.044
Everyone keep moving
in an orderly fashion!

559
00:35:11.128 --> 00:35:12.254
Allison!

560
00:35:13.130 --> 00:35:14.881
Do not run!

561
00:35:16.299 --> 00:35:18.176
Okay. Thank you. Lieutenant.

562
00:35:20.220 --> 00:35:22.722
Ma'am. they're boarding.
There's nothing more I can do for you.

563
00:35:22.806 --> 00:35:25.517
No. no. no. Come on. You can go on
one of those planes and look for him.

564
00:35:25.600 --> 00:35:28.979
There are dozens of planes with
over 2.000 passengers crammed in.

565
00:35:29.062 --> 00:35:31.565
- I can't hold them up for this.
- Are there phones? Can I call?

566
00:35:31.648 --> 00:35:33.650
I don't know
if there's any phones.

567
00:35:33.733 --> 00:35:36.361
- Where are these planes going?
- Shelter destinations are classified.

568
00:35:36.445 --> 00:35:39.281
Look. ma'am. this is an emergency
operation with a lot of moving parts.

569
00:35:39.364 --> 00:35:42.075
I am just in transport.
I wish I had more answers for you.

570
00:35:42.159 --> 00:35:43.743
Please.
What am I supposed to do?

571
00:35:43.827 --> 00:35:46.204
- I'm very sorry.
- Stop. stop. No. no. no!

572
00:35:46.288 --> 00:35:49.416
Ma'am. I need you to step this
way. please.

573
00:35:56.089 --> 00:35:57.424
Allison!

574
00:35:57.507 --> 00:35:58.758
Nathan!

575
00:36:00.719 --> 00:36:02.012
Allison!

576
00:36:02.929 --> 00:36:04.222
Nathan!

577
00:36:05.932 --> 00:36:07.225
Nathan!

578
00:36:07.684 --> 00:36:09.311
Allison!

579
00:36:09.394 --> 00:36:11.605
Everybody sit down!
Let's go. let's go!

580
00:36:11.688 --> 00:36:13.523
Everyone sit.

581
00:36:13.607 --> 00:36:16.276
Everyone find a seat. Sir. find a seat.
We're ready to roll.

582
00:36:16.359 --> 00:36:18.695
I'm trying to find my wife and kid.
They're on this plane.

583
00:36:18.778 --> 00:36:21.281
I need you to sit down.
We gotta get wheels up.

584
00:36:21.364 --> 00:36:25.285
Everybody find a seat. Sit down. sir!
Find a seat. Let's go!

585
00:36:31.875 --> 00:36:33.043
Shit.

586
00:36:46.014 --> 00:36:47.015
Come on.

587
00:37:02.531 --> 00:37:05.575
Hey. Hey.
Hey. how'd you get on?

588
00:37:07.410 --> 00:37:09.746
What do you mean?
I was selected.

589
00:37:09.829 --> 00:37:11.373
Yeah. I know.
With those.

590
00:37:12.374 --> 00:37:14.501
No. it's my son's.

591
00:37:14.584 --> 00:37:16.211
He's diabetic.

592
00:37:16.294 --> 00:37:18.797
Yeah. so is my sister's kid.
and they turned him away.

593
00:37:18.880 --> 00:37:20.423
They said no illnesses.

594
00:37:20.507 --> 00:37:23.134
Do you know somebody
who can help us?

595
00:37:28.181 --> 00:37:30.475
Hey! No. wait. wait. wait!

596
00:37:30.559 --> 00:37:32.519
No. open that door!

597
00:37:32.602 --> 00:37:34.813
- Open that door! No!
- Whoa. whoa!

598
00:37:34.896 --> 00:37:36.898
What are you doing. sir?
Get back in your seat.

599
00:37:36.982 --> 00:37:38.858
- Get back in your seat!
- You gotta let me out.

600
00:37:38.942 --> 00:37:41.861
I've gotta get to my kid.
please. I beg you.

601
00:37:41.945 --> 00:37:44.155
You get off this plane.
we are leaving without you.

602
00:37:44.239 --> 00:37:46.950
That's okay.
Just let me off the plane!

603
00:37:47.033 --> 00:37:49.494
Thank you.

604
00:37:49.578 --> 00:37:50.579
Thank you.

605
00:37:52.122 --> 00:37:53.123
Sorry.

606
00:38:00.088 --> 00:38:02.465
Perimeter breach!
Perimeter breach!

607
00:38:02.549 --> 00:38:05.343
- Ma'am. step this way! Somebody help her!
- Perimeter breach!

608
00:38:05.427 --> 00:38:07.220
Move. move. move!

609
00:38:07.304 --> 00:38:08.388
Security breach!

610
00:38:08.471 --> 00:38:10.098
It's okay.
Come on. Let's go.

611
00:38:11.975 --> 00:38:15.312
Perimeter breach.
Perimeter breach. Runway three-three.

612
00:38:15.395 --> 00:38:17.522
All security forces
to runway three-three.

613
00:38:20.567 --> 00:38:24.487
- Go. go! Runway 33!
- Maintain the perimeter!

614
00:38:24.571 --> 00:38:26.197
Backup to runway 33!

615
00:38:26.281 --> 00:38:27.532
Follow me!

616
00:38:33.622 --> 00:38:35.832
- Let me on that plane!
- Let us on!

617
00:38:35.915 --> 00:38:38.126
- Please take us!
- Let us on!

618
00:38:38.209 --> 00:38:41.212
- Drop your weapons!
- Drop your weapons!

619
00:38:41.296 --> 00:38:42.922
Drop it!

620
00:38:45.258 --> 00:38:46.635
Stay there! Get on the ground!

621
00:38:47.802 --> 00:38:49.554
Drop your weapons now!

622
00:38:55.852 --> 00:38:59.147
Hey! Everybody get out!
There's fuel leaking. It's not safe!

623
00:38:59.230 --> 00:39:00.231
Go!

624
00:39:01.566 --> 00:39:02.942
Get on the ground!

625
00:39:07.197 --> 00:39:08.198
Go. go. go!

626
00:39:34.933 --> 00:39:36.017
Is that Dad's plane?

627
00:39:37.936 --> 00:39:39.646
No. honey.
See. there's other planes.

628
00:39:39.729 --> 00:39:41.981
He's not on that one. okay?

629
00:39:44.317 --> 00:39:46.820
We'll find him. Come on.
Come on. Hold my hand.

630
00:39:57.163 --> 00:39:58.748
- Get out!
- Hurry! Don't stop!

631
00:39:58.832 --> 00:40:00.458
Let's go! Move back!

632
00:40:00.542 --> 00:40:03.670
- Hey. sir. don't stop!
- Hey. hey. hey.

633
00:40:03.753 --> 00:40:07.382
Stop and listen! I need to find my wife
and kid. Did they come through here?

634
00:40:07.465 --> 00:40:09.050
Sir. I remember you.

635
00:40:09.134 --> 00:40:10.969
They declined your son.
Your family's not out there.

636
00:40:12.804 --> 00:40:14.097
Keep moving back.

637
00:40:14.180 --> 00:40:15.598
Move back!

638
00:40:15.682 --> 00:40:17.600
Go. go. go.

639
00:40:19.519 --> 00:40:21.104
Oh. shit.

640
00:40:24.107 --> 00:40:25.650
Careful.

641
00:40:25.734 --> 00:40:27.736
Stand over here.
away from the glass.

642
00:40:28.528 --> 00:40:30.113
Come on! Over here!

643
00:40:30.905 --> 00:40:32.407
Are you okay?

644
00:40:32.490 --> 00:40:34.284
Let me see.
Look at me.

645
00:40:35.577 --> 00:40:36.870
Are you low?

646
00:40:38.538 --> 00:40:39.664
Empty.

647
00:40:39.748 --> 00:40:41.666
Hold on.
let me find your meds.

648
00:40:42.584 --> 00:40:44.210
Your dad must have them.

649
00:40:44.294 --> 00:40:46.337
Okay. Look at me.

650
00:40:46.421 --> 00:40:48.757
All right.
we've gotta find a pharmacy.

651
00:40:48.840 --> 00:40:50.133
Here.

652
00:40:50.216 --> 00:40:52.260
Here. take that.

653
00:40:52.343 --> 00:40:55.555
If we don't find Daddy.
we'll go to Grandpa's house. okay?

654
00:40:55.638 --> 00:40:57.474
I'm just gonna
send him a message.

655
00:41:05.732 --> 00:41:08.526
Stay back!

656
00:41:23.166 --> 00:41:24.417
Oh. shit.

657
00:41:55.156 --> 00:41:56.241
Allison!

658
00:42:45.832 --> 00:42:46.875
Okay. there it is.

659
00:42:50.336 --> 00:42:52.881
All right. You've gotta
stay really close to me. okay?

660
00:43:14.527 --> 00:43:17.238
Get what we need and get out
of here as quick as possible.

661
00:43:20.241 --> 00:43:21.242
Sorry.

662
00:43:28.875 --> 00:43:30.710
Here. Okay.

663
00:43:30.793 --> 00:43:32.587
Come on.
Kneel down with me.

664
00:43:33.254 --> 00:43:34.255
Okay.

665
00:43:36.633 --> 00:43:38.676
Give me your finger.

666
00:43:38.760 --> 00:43:40.970
You're such a brave guy.
you know that?

667
00:43:42.972 --> 00:43:44.390
Oh. Jesus.
You're at 300.

668
00:43:46.100 --> 00:43:47.435
Let's get you fixed up.

669
00:43:53.691 --> 00:43:55.860
Okay.

670
00:44:07.413 --> 00:44:08.414
Okay.

671
00:44:15.964 --> 00:44:18.299
Come on!
Everybody out! Come on!

672
00:44:18.383 --> 00:44:20.510
Get out!

673
00:44:20.593 --> 00:44:22.512
Get out of here!

674
00:44:22.595 --> 00:44:24.847
- Move! Get out! Get out!
- Get the hell out!

675
00:44:26.015 --> 00:44:28.768
- Everybody out now! Let's go!
- Get moving!

676
00:44:28.851 --> 00:44:31.062
- Move!
- Move. bitch! Get out!

677
00:44:32.981 --> 00:44:34.399
Move!

678
00:44:34.482 --> 00:44:36.109
We're just gonna go
as fast as we can. okay?

679
00:44:36.192 --> 00:44:37.902
Just stay low.
Stay next to me.

680
00:44:37.986 --> 00:44:40.154
Come on. now.
Come on. come on. come on.

681
00:44:44.867 --> 00:44:46.035
Let's go! Come on!

682
00:44:47.495 --> 00:44:48.663
Just grab it all!

683
00:44:48.746 --> 00:44:49.747
Come on. keep moving!

684
00:44:53.126 --> 00:44:54.961
No. no. no!

685
00:44:55.044 --> 00:44:56.295
Oh. my God!

686
00:44:57.005 --> 00:44:58.339
No. don't look.

687
00:44:58.423 --> 00:44:59.882
Don't look.

688
00:45:00.508 --> 00:45:02.051
Oh. my God.

689
00:45:02.135 --> 00:45:04.262
Here. stay with me. Stay
with me. right next to me.

690
00:45:08.850 --> 00:45:11.102
Please! Please.

691
00:45:11.185 --> 00:45:12.687
- Please.
- Move!

692
00:45:12.770 --> 00:45:15.231
My son's only seven years old!

693
00:45:15.314 --> 00:45:16.315
Move it. move!

694
00:45:21.070 --> 00:45:22.071
Go.

695
00:45:22.697 --> 00:45:23.948
Come on!

696
00:45:28.911 --> 00:45:30.580
Hey!

697
00:45:30.663 --> 00:45:33.041
Hey. hey!
Are you going up north?

698
00:45:33.124 --> 00:45:35.334
Please. we need a ride. Please.

699
00:45:35.418 --> 00:45:37.170
- Are you going up north?
- Get in the car.

700
00:45:37.253 --> 00:45:38.629
No. no. no!

701
00:45:38.713 --> 00:45:41.340
No. we just need to get
up near Lexington.

702
00:45:41.424 --> 00:45:43.009
Get in the car.

703
00:45:43.092 --> 00:45:44.552
I'll take you as far as
Knoxville. but that's it.

704
00:45:44.635 --> 00:45:46.679
Thank you!
Get in. get in. get in!

705
00:45:46.763 --> 00:45:48.890
- Come on. Get on in. son.
- Okay.

706
00:45:58.900 --> 00:46:01.486
- My God. Could you hear gunfire?
- Yes.

707
00:46:01.569 --> 00:46:03.571
I just started running.

708
00:46:03.654 --> 00:46:05.698
I turn around. and there was an old
woman who'd been in a wheelchair.

709
00:46:05.782 --> 00:46:08.284
- They just killed her.
- Oh. Jesus.

710
00:46:08.367 --> 00:46:10.328
I watched them. I thought
they were gonna shoot me.

711
00:46:10.411 --> 00:46:12.413
- I'm sorry. hon.
- All right. there you go.

712
00:46:12.497 --> 00:46:14.082
- You're okay. Okay?
- Okay.

713
00:46:14.165 --> 00:46:16.375
- Are you okay back there?
- Yes.

714
00:46:16.459 --> 00:46:18.211
Thank you so much.

715
00:46:18.294 --> 00:46:21.339
It's like there's no chain of command.
Nobody in charge.

716
00:46:21.422 --> 00:46:23.341
Everybody's running around
with their heads cut off.

717
00:46:23.424 --> 00:46:24.759
Shit.

718
00:46:24.842 --> 00:46:26.385
We'll get to Knoxville.
get on a flight.

719
00:46:26.469 --> 00:46:28.346
Yeah. if we can get there
before they take off.

720
00:46:28.429 --> 00:46:30.848
And if they let us through.

721
00:46:30.932 --> 00:46:33.267
I mean. that stupid lottery.

722
00:46:33.351 --> 00:46:36.229
You know the government
knew about all this.

723
00:46:36.312 --> 00:46:38.898
and all they did
was pick the rich fat cats.

724
00:46:38.981 --> 00:46:40.191
Damn.

725
00:46:41.984 --> 00:46:43.778
Hey. is your son.
is he hungry?

726
00:46:43.861 --> 00:46:45.988
- We got a sandwich here.
- Oh.

727
00:46:46.072 --> 00:46:48.533
You know what? It would be really good
for him to eat something. Thank you.

728
00:46:48.616 --> 00:46:51.244
We got a turkey sandwich. sweetheart.
Does that sound nice?

729
00:46:51.327 --> 00:46:52.829
- Thank you.
- Mm-hmm.

730
00:46:53.830 --> 00:46:55.164
What do we say?

731
00:46:55.248 --> 00:46:56.916
What do you say. sweetheart?

732
00:46:56.999 --> 00:46:58.042
Thank you.

733
00:46:58.126 --> 00:47:00.169
Well. you are welcome. pal.

734
