through here.

985
01:08:22.951 --> 01:08:25.995
Look. maybe try the FEMA camp
across the street.

986
01:08:46.975 --> 01:08:48.351
Move! Move!

987
01:08:48.435 --> 01:08:50.311
You need to fill out
this consent form.

988
01:08:50.395 --> 01:08:52.939
The soldier at the checkpoint
said you might have my son here.

989
01:08:53.022 --> 01:08:54.816
- You need to wait in line.
- Listen to me!

990
01:08:54.899 --> 01:08:56.359
You need to wait in line!

991
01:08:56.443 --> 01:08:58.528
- I need to find my son.
- We're doing our best.

992
01:08:58.611 --> 01:09:01.448
He's seven years old! He was taken from me!
Somebody just listen to me!

993
01:09:01.531 --> 01:09:03.283
Ma'am. Please.
Come here. Talk to me.

994
01:09:03.366 --> 01:09:05.285
- What's going on?
- I'm trying to find my son.

995
01:09:05.368 --> 01:09:07.704
He's seven years old. He's diabetic.
He was taken from me.

996
01:09:07.787 --> 01:09:09.706
Somebody said
he could be over here.

997
01:09:09.789 --> 01:09:12.125
I'll help you find your son.
but you need to calm down. Follow me.

998
01:09:16.838 --> 01:09:18.423
Let's check the pediatric tent.

999
01:09:22.135 --> 01:09:23.386
- Where? Where?
- Right here.

1000
01:09:23.470 --> 01:09:24.471
- This one?
- Yes.

1001
01:09:27.140 --> 01:09:29.225
You see him?

1002
01:09:29.309 --> 01:09:31.436
- No. he's not in there.
- Let's try around here.

1003
01:09:39.360 --> 01:09:40.361
You see him?

1004
01:09:40.445 --> 01:09:41.488
No. he's not in here.

1005
01:09:44.657 --> 01:09:46.910
- How about here?
- No. he's not here either.

1006
01:09:46.993 --> 01:09:48.745
It's okay. It's okay.
We'll find him.

1007
01:09:48.828 --> 01:09:50.371
Check this one here.

1008
01:10:07.680 --> 01:10:10.600
Nathan! Nathan.

1009
01:10:10.683 --> 01:10:13.603
- Mom!
- Oh. honey! Oh. my God.

1010
01:10:13.686 --> 01:10:14.687
Look at me.

1011
01:10:15.355 --> 01:10:16.523
Oh. baby.

1012
01:10:17.524 --> 01:10:20.235
I'm so sorry!

1013
01:10:21.694 --> 01:10:23.154
Oh. my God!

1014
01:10:24.656 --> 01:10:26.115
I'm so sorry.

1015
01:10:26.866 --> 01:10:28.159
I'm so sorry.

1016
01:10:30.286 --> 01:10:33.039
I'll never let that happen again.
I'm so sorry.

1017
01:10:35.625 --> 01:10:37.210
I'm fine. Mom.

1018
01:10:37.293 --> 01:10:39.087
He's a remarkable young man.

1019
01:10:40.713 --> 01:10:42.549
- You're Allison.
- Yeah.

1020
01:10:42.632 --> 01:10:45.802
He's type one diabetic.
I've gotta check his levels.

1021
01:10:45.885 --> 01:10:47.220
He told us.

1022
01:10:47.303 --> 01:10:49.097
We checked his levels twice.

1023
01:10:49.180 --> 01:10:51.140
Gave him some insulin.
new pump.

1024
01:10:51.224 --> 01:10:53.142
If I can get you
to sign this release form.

1025
01:10:53.226 --> 01:10:55.478
I can move you guys
into a family tent.

1026
01:10:58.189 --> 01:11:01.401
No. we're going
to my father's.

1027
01:11:01.484 --> 01:11:05.238
I lost my... I lost my husband.
We're gonna find him.

1028
01:11:05.321 --> 01:11:06.864
I'm so sorry.

1029
01:11:06.948 --> 01:11:08.324
Where does your father live?

1030
01:11:09.409 --> 01:11:12.120
In Lexington.
Near Lexington.

1031
01:11:12.203 --> 01:11:16.457
Okay. Maybe I can get you on a
military bus heading in that direction.

1032
01:11:16.541 --> 01:11:19.294
And I also put together a
week's supply of glucose tabs.

1033
01:11:19.377 --> 01:11:21.879
and insulin.
and test strips. so...

1034
01:11:21.963 --> 01:11:25.425
I wish I could give you
more. but it's all we have.

1035
01:11:27.427 --> 01:11:29.220
Thank you.

1036
01:12:14.140 --> 01:12:15.141
Hello?

1037
01:12:16.392 --> 01:12:17.644
Hello?

1038
01:12:59.268 --> 01:13:02.522
<i>...see on camera at this moment.
but the city is mostly burning...</i>

1039
01:13:02.605 --> 01:13:05.942
<i>Governments continue to struggle
to contain the social chao...</i>

1040
01:13:06.025 --> 01:13:09.028
<i>...again. this livestream
video that's gone viral.</i>

1041
01:13:09.112 --> 01:13:12.115
<i>We have to warn you.
these images are disturbing.</i>

1042
01:13:12.198 --> 01:13:14.701
<i>All of downtown is on fire. man.</i>

1043
01:13:14.784 --> 01:13:16.452
<i>Check it out.
There's another one.</i>

1044
01:13:18.955 --> 01:13:21.290
<i>Wait. Is that coming
towards us? Wait. Holy...</i>

1045
01:13:21.374 --> 01:13:22.542
<i>Yo. run!</i>

1046
01:13:24.877 --> 01:13:26.879
<i>Yet another shocking image...</i>

1047
01:13:26.963 --> 01:13:29.257
- <i>Sometimes they come down...</i>
- <i>Wow.</i>

1048
01:13:29.340 --> 01:13:32.176
<i>They come out of nowhere. you know?
There's no warning.</i>

1049
01:13:32.260 --> 01:13:34.303
- <i>We're just trying to keep up.</i>
- <i>Yeah.</i>

1050
01:13:34.387 --> 01:13:36.013
<i>And. uh...</i>

1051
01:13:36.097 --> 01:13:39.016
<i>having in the back of our head
that tomorrow we're...</i>

1052
01:13:39.100 --> 01:13:42.103
<i>It's all gonna be for nothing.</i>

1053
01:15:18.699 --> 01:15:20.076
Now it comes.

1054
01:15:47.353 --> 01:15:48.813
<i>What a load of shit.</i>

1055
01:15:53.067 --> 01:15:56.404
<i>Looks like I'm gonna have to
dip into my savings for this next round.</i>

1056
01:16:00.366 --> 01:16:03.703
You're alone.
Where's Allison?

1057
01:16:03.786 --> 01:16:06.038
- Where is she?
- I was hoping she'd be here.

1058
01:16:06.122 --> 01:16:08.416
Why are my friends stuck here
babysitting me

1059
01:16:08.499 --> 01:16:11.502
while my daughter and grandson
are out there alone.

1060
01:16:11.586 --> 01:16:13.754
and I'm here
with no way to find them?

1061
01:16:13.838 --> 01:16:17.008
We lost each other at the airfield.
and she left me a note to meet her here.

1062
01:16:17.091 --> 01:16:19.051
Fuck.

1063
01:16:22.513 --> 01:16:24.056
Maybe we should go.

1064
01:16:24.140 --> 01:16:26.767
She told me you were
moving back in.

1065
01:16:26.851 --> 01:16:29.395
Let me guess.
you had another fight?

1066
01:16:29.478 --> 01:16:32.857
We both want the same thing.
okay. for them to get here safely.

1067
01:16:32.940 --> 01:16:35.401
So why don't we try
to work together?

1068
01:16:35.484 --> 01:16:36.652
Okay.

1069
01:16:36.736 --> 01:16:39.155
Okay. Did you try the landline?

1070
01:16:40.239 --> 01:16:42.700
Go ahead. I tried
about an hour ago again.

1071
01:16:42.783 --> 01:16:44.535
Keeps going
straight to voice mail.

1072
01:16:44.619 --> 01:16:47.038
Or you get that
stupid government message.

1073
01:16:48.789 --> 01:16:52.251
God. you would think
technology would work in emergencies.

1074
01:16:57.173 --> 01:16:58.174
Hey.

1075
01:17:00.468 --> 01:17:01.552
What happened to you?

1076
01:17:01.636 --> 01:17:03.429
- Nothing.
- Come on.

1077
01:17:05.890 --> 01:17:07.391
It's been a long day.

1078
01:17:09.644 --> 01:17:11.395
Just want 'em back.
I just...

1079
01:17:58.359 --> 01:18:01.028
Okay. there's a pay phone there.
Let's try that.

1080
01:18:08.160 --> 01:18:09.161
Yes.

1081
01:18:14.875 --> 01:18:18.129
Hello? Where? Stay there.
Stay right there.

1082
01:18:18.212 --> 01:18:20.631
- Where are they?
- Down the road. Let's go.

1083
01:18:39.275 --> 01:18:40.276
Hey.

1084
01:18:49.994 --> 01:18:52.329
I'm sorry. honey.
I tried. I tried.

1085
01:18:53.914 --> 01:18:55.124
I know. It's okay.

1086
01:18:56.125 --> 01:18:57.126
Kiddo.

1087
01:18:57.209 --> 01:18:58.836
- How you doing?
- Good.

1088
01:18:58.919 --> 01:19:00.671
Yeah? Here.

1089
01:19:00.755 --> 01:19:03.966
Come here.
How you doing? Okay?

1090
01:19:04.050 --> 01:19:06.093
Thanks for looking after
your mom. bud.

1091
01:19:12.141 --> 01:19:13.517
Hi. Dad.

1092
01:19:13.601 --> 01:19:15.603
Hey. sunflower.

1093
01:19:22.276 --> 01:19:24.487
Oh.

1094
01:19:29.366 --> 01:19:31.577
Come on. honey.
Let's get you guys home.

1095
01:19:32.161 --> 01:19:33.621
Okay.

1096
01:19:36.540 --> 01:19:37.792
Come on.

1097
01:19:40.878 --> 01:19:44.298
All right. welcome. You hungry?
What do you wanna eat?

1098
01:19:44.381 --> 01:19:46.425
- Pancakes.
- Pancakes. Syrup?

1099
01:19:46.509 --> 01:19:47.593
- Yeah!
- Yeah!

1100
01:19:47.676 --> 01:19:49.345
- No.
- No.

1101
01:19:49.428 --> 01:19:51.138
- No. I forgot.
- We don't have enough insulin as it is.

1102
01:19:51.222 --> 01:19:52.515
Aw!

1103
01:19:52.598 --> 01:19:54.850
- I have his medication here.
- You do?

1104
01:19:54.934 --> 01:19:58.270
Yeah. It was out of the fridge for a
long time. but it should still be good.

1105
01:19:58.354 --> 01:19:59.355
Thank you.

1106
01:20:01.398 --> 01:20:04.193
You remember where this goes?

1107
01:20:04.276 --> 01:20:06.987
- What do you want? Some water?
- Some water. yeah.

1108
01:20:07.905 --> 01:20:09.406
Way to go. All right!

1109
01:20:09.490 --> 01:20:11.659
- This good?
- Yep! Perfect.

1110
01:20:11.742 --> 01:20:14.829
- "Perfectomundo."
- We should check the news.

1111
01:20:14.912 --> 01:20:17.039
What do you think?

1112
01:20:17.123 --> 01:20:20.668
<i>At approximately 8:47 a.m.
Eastern Standard Time tomorrow.</i>

1113
01:20:20.751 --> 01:20:23.504
<i>the largest fragment from
Clarke is expected to land</i>

1114
01:20:23.587 --> 01:20:26.048
<i>somewhere between
North Africa and Europe.</i>

1115
01:20:26.132 --> 01:20:29.301
<i>Space agencies tracking
this fragment are predicting</i>

1116
01:20:29.385 --> 01:20:33.806
<i>an extinction-level event
to extend around the globe.</i>

1117
01:20:33.889 --> 01:20:36.851
<i>giving the limited number of
people chosen by their skill sets</i>

1118
01:20:36.934 --> 01:20:39.019
<i>the greatest chance of survival.</i>

1119
01:20:39.103 --> 01:20:42.773
<i>Here again is the classified
footage discovered earlier today</i>

1120
01:20:42.857 --> 01:20:47.653
<i>showing the sophistication of five bunkers
near Thule Air Force Base in Greenland.</i>

1121
01:20:47.736 --> 01:20:49.405
They are in Greenland.

1122
01:20:49.488 --> 01:20:51.490
<i>Built during the Cold War
in case of nuclear fallout...</i>

1123
01:20:51.574 --> 01:20:53.742
- He was right.
- Who was right?

1124
01:20:53.826 --> 01:20:55.911
<i>...the bunkers are self-sufficient
with underground water tanks...</i>

1125
01:20:55.995 --> 01:20:58.164
Just this really good guy.

1126
01:20:58.247 --> 01:21:01.292
<i>...hydroponic seed farms.
medical supplies and oxygen generators.</i>

1127
01:21:01.375 --> 01:21:04.003
- A lot of good that'll do us now.
- The footage is older than me.

1128
01:21:04.086 --> 01:21:05.796
Who knows
what shape it's in?

1129
01:21:05.880 --> 01:21:07.381
At least here
we'll be together.

1130
01:21:08.716 --> 01:21:09.925
What are you doing. John?

1131
01:21:11.010 --> 01:21:12.887
There's another way
for us to get there.

1132
01:21:12.970 --> 01:21:15.306
- Where?
- To Greenland.

1133
01:21:15.389 --> 01:21:17.516
There are pilots going
from up in Canada.

1134
01:21:17.600 --> 01:21:19.351
They're taking people.
They're not military.

1135
01:21:19.435 --> 01:21:22.104
Look. it's just over
12 hours to Osgoode.

1136
01:21:22.188 --> 01:21:23.939
But we can do it in nine.

1137
01:21:24.023 --> 01:21:26.317
And then it's another six to
eight hours for the flight.

1138
01:21:27.026 --> 01:21:29.153
We can make this.

1139
01:21:29.236 --> 01:21:31.238
My bracelet. What if they don't let us in?
They've already flagged Nathan.

1140
01:21:31.322 --> 01:21:33.073
Honey. it's our only chance.

1141
01:21:33.157 --> 01:21:35.951
Now listen. We can either stay
here or we can give it a shot.

1142
01:21:36.035 --> 01:21:39.371
But if we give it a shot.
I swear I will get us into those bunkers.

1143
01:21:40.581 --> 01:21:42.625
But if we're gonna go.

1144
01:21:42.708 --> 01:21:44.251
we gotta go now.

1145
01:21:46.086 --> 01:21:47.588
- Okay.
- Okay.

1146
01:21:47.671 --> 01:21:49.548
- Okay. Let's do it.
- All right.

1147
01:21:49.632 --> 01:21:51.592
Nathan. let's get ready.
We left some clothes in the guest room.

1148
01:21:51.675 --> 01:21:53.219
What about the pancakes?

1149
01:21:53.302 --> 01:21:55.763
I'll make 'em. Don't worry.
They're on their way.

1150
01:22:04.688 --> 01:22:06.482
Okay. Nathan.

1151
01:22:06.565 --> 01:22:08.192
Go ahead.
take your clothes off.

1152
01:22:08.275 --> 01:22:10.110
There you go.
All right. step in.

1153
01:22:10.194 --> 01:22:12.196
Shampoo's over there.
Grab that.

1154
01:22:12.279 --> 01:22:14.573
Okay. Go ahead.
Wash yourself.

1155
01:22:16.617 --> 01:22:17.618
Good job.

1156
01:22:18.494 --> 01:22:19.787
Okay. Hurry up.

1157
01:22:25.417 --> 01:22:27.169
Hey.

1158
01:22:36.345 --> 01:22:38.055
You need to pack some clothes. Dale.

1159
01:22:38.138 --> 01:22:40.432
We barely have
enough time as it is.

1160
01:22:40.516 --> 01:22:43.143
Somebody's gotta stay
and watch Beck.

1161
01:22:43.227 --> 01:22:45.688
Mary'd kill me if I left him.

1162
01:22:46.522 --> 01:22:49.149
Man. she spent hours in here.

1163
01:22:49.233 --> 01:22:53.988
Now I can't separate the smell
from my memory of her anymore.

1164
01:22:54.071 --> 01:22:55.489
God.

1165
01:22:55.572 --> 01:22:57.199
Hay and horse shit.

1166
01:22:58.784 --> 01:23:00.619
Dale.

1167
01:23:00.703 --> 01:23:03.622
this isn't some storm
you can ride out.

1168
01:23:05.874 --> 01:23:06.875
Look...

1169
01:23:08.377 --> 01:23:11.130
I don't fold
when things get rough.

1170
01:23:14.383 --> 01:23:17.261
I know you guys' marriage
was on the rocks.

1171
01:23:17.344 --> 01:23:19.513
Every marriage
goes through shit.

1172
01:23:19.596 --> 01:23:22.266
Every marriage
goes through shit.

1173
01:23:22.349 --> 01:23:26.937
That don't mean you get to
jump into another woman's bed.

1174
01:23:29.857 --> 01:23:31.358
You're right. I did.

1175
01:23:32.985 --> 01:23:36.363
And I'm gonna have to live with
that for the rest of my life.

1176
01:23:37.448 --> 01:23:39.867
I'm not expecting
your forgiveness. Dale.

1177
01:23:41.201 --> 01:23:43.996
But if I get one thing right.

1178
01:23:44.079 --> 01:23:47.416
I'm gonna get my son
and my wife into that bunker.

1179
01:24:01.722 --> 01:24:03.140
Please come with us.

1180
01:24:04.058 --> 01:24:05.476
No.

1181
01:24:05.559 --> 01:24:07.728
Why are you being
so stubborn? Just come.

1182
01:24:07.811 --> 01:24:09.438
You know
you'll die here. Dale.

1183
01:24:09.521 --> 01:24:11.482
Of course I will.

1184
01:24:11.565 --> 01:24:15.444
Today. tomorrow. 10 years from now.
don't make no difference to me.

1185
01:24:15.527 --> 01:24:18.614
My Mary went to heaven
in this place.

1186
01:24:20.783 --> 01:24:23.202
And when the good Lord's ready
for me to join her.

1187
01:24:23.285 --> 01:24:26.705
I'm gonna be right here
in this place too...

1188
01:24:28.248 --> 01:24:29.750
bags packed.

1189
01:24:44.723 --> 01:24:45.808
Nathan!

1190
01:24:50.729 --> 01:24:51.897
Nathan!

1191
01:24:55.442 --> 01:24:56.693
Nathan!

1192
01:24:56.777 --> 01:24:58.779
Hey. Kiddo. are you hurt?

1193
01:24:58.862 --> 01:25:01.115
How close do you think that hit?

1194
01:25:01.198 --> 01:25:02.741
Anything hit you?
That was close.

1195
01:25:02.825 --> 01:25:05.035
All right.
we gotta get out of here now.

1196
01:25:05.119 --> 01:25:07.371
Take my truck.
It's got a full tank of gas.

1197
01:25:13.210 --> 01:25:15.212
Hold on. hold on.
Let me get your booster.

1198
01:25:16.088 --> 01:25:17.714
Up you go.

1199
01:25:20.467 --> 01:25:22.386
Take care of them.

1200
01:25:23.220 --> 01:25:24.221
I will.

1201
01:25:24.304 --> 01:25:26.432
I know you will. son.

1202
01:25:30.727 --> 01:25:31.728
Bye.

1203
01:25:41.697 --> 01:25:43.949
When will I ever see you
again. Grandpa?

1204
01:25:45.868 --> 01:25:46.994
Grandpa...

1205
01:25:47.077 --> 01:25:48.996
Yeah. pretty soon.

1206
01:25:49.079 --> 01:25:52.708
All this blows over. I'll come
up. visit you and the polar bears.

1207
01:25:53.709 --> 01:25:55.252
Polar bears?

1208
01:25:55.335 --> 01:25:58.422
Well. yeah. You're going
to the North Pole. right?

1209
01:25:58.505 --> 01:26:01.300
Say hi to Santa for me.

1210
01:26:01.383 --> 01:26:04.303
Tell him
I'm still mad about the coal.

1211
01:26:18.317 --> 01:26:21.445
I-I love you. sunflower.

1212
01:26:23.113 --> 01:26:24.573
I love you too. Dad.

1213
01:26:34.917 --> 01:26:36.585
Mom would have been proud.

1214
01:26:37.961 --> 01:26:38.962
Of what?

1215
01:26:39.922 --> 01:26:41.590
You finished the house.

1216
01:26:47.513 --> 01:26:48.514
Bye.

1217
01:27:12.371 --> 01:27:13.747
Bye. Grandpa.

1218
01:28:02.296 --> 01:28:04.339
My friend Teddy says

1219
01:28:04.423 --> 01:28:07.301
your life flashes in front
of your eyes when you die.

1220
01:28:10.887 --> 01:28:14.725
I think it would be better if
it did that while you lived.

1221
01:28:14.808 --> 01:28:17.978
That way. you could see all
the good memories and be happy.

1222
01:28:19.896 --> 01:28:22.149
I like that idea a lot.

1223
01:28:22.232 --> 01:28:23.233
Me too.

1224
01:28:24.026 --> 01:28:26.028
How'd you get to be so smart?

1225
01:28:38.957 --> 01:28:42.127
<i>World leaders scramble to
create makeshift shelters</i>

1226
01:28:42.210 --> 01:28:45.297
<i>as Clarke's largest fragment.
